{"title": "Far Away and Long Ago - A History of My Early Life (Version 2)", "description": " A boy (between the ages of 4 and 12) discovers the natural world around him in his home in the Argentine Pampas and in Buenos Aires. Author Hudson is best known for Green Mansions but is considered by Argentine readers as one of their own, for his \u201cFar and Away\u2026\u201d and many other works highlighting South America. As a budding naturalist, Hudson was given total freedom to discover the wonders of his world. Earnest Hemingway reportedly admired Hudson\u2019s works and even named a character in one of his books after him. This work is filled with discoveries and memorable characters, vividly portrayed. - Summary by John Greenman", "duration": 37690, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2664", "name": "William Henry Hudson"}], "coverArt": null, "copyright_year": "1918", "genres": ["Animals", "Nature", "Social Science (Culture & Anthropology)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "John Greenman"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "John Greenman"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "DaveC"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Larry Wilson"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I - Earliest Memories", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/farawayandlongagover2_2402_librivox/farawayandlongago2_01_hudson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1882}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II - My New Home", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/farawayandlongagover2_2402_librivox/farawayandlongago2_02_hudson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1677}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter III - Death of an Old Dog", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/farawayandlongagover2_2402_librivox/farawayandlongago2_03_hudson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1495}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter IV - The Plantation", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/farawayandlongagover2_2402_librivox/farawayandlongago2_04